# AEGIS Sentinel — ESP32 Firmware README

## Overview

**AEGIS Sentinel v6.0** is the ESP32 firmware for a real-time IoT environmental monitoring system. It reads temperature/humidity from a DHT11 sensor and gas concentration from an MQ gas sensor, then pushes live data to Firebase Realtime Database while fetching control commands from a Railway.app HTTP backend.

---

## Hardware Required

| Component | Pin | Notes |
|-----------|-----|-------|
| MQ Gas Sensor | GPIO 34 (AOUT) | Needs 5V VCC, not 3.3V |
| DHT11 | GPIO 25 | Needs 10kΩ pull-up resistor to VCC |
| Buzzer (passive) | GPIO 27 | Uses tone() function |
| LED (alarm) | GPIO 26 | Use 220Ω series resistor |
| Relay (fan) | GPIO 14 | Active LOW — LOW = fan ON |

### Wiring Quick Reference

```
DHT11:
  VCC  → 3.3V or 5V
  GND  → GND
  DATA → GPIO 25 + 10kΩ resistor to VCC

MQ Gas Sensor:
  VCC  → 5V  (MUST be 5V, not 3.3V)
  GND  → GND
  AOUT → GPIO 34

Buzzer:
  (+)  → GPIO 27
  (-)  → GND

LED:
  (+)  → GPIO 26 → 220Ω → LED anode
  (-)  → GND

Relay Module:
  VCC  → 5V
  GND  → GND
  IN   → GPIO 14
  COM  → Fan power line
  NO   → Fan (Normally Open)
```

