## Firebase Data Structure

ESP32 writes to `/sensors` node every 1 second:

```json
{
  "temp": 28.5,
  "humidity": 62.0,
  "gas": 320,
  "fan": false,
  "alarm": false,
  "dhtOK": true,
  "mode": "auto",
  "muted": false,
  "emergency": false,
  "fanTimerActive": false,
  "fanRemaining": 0,
  "buzzerActive": false,
  "buzzerRemaining": 0,
  "uptime": 1234
}
```

ESP32 reads from `/control` node via Railway (not directly from Firebase).

---

## Railway Control Commands

ESP32 fetches `GET /control` from Railway every 2 seconds:

```json
{
  "mode": "auto",
  "fan": false,
  "mute": false,
  "forceStopFan": false,
  "forceStopBuzz": false,
  "emergencyStop": false
}
```

---

## Firebase Rules

Set in Firebase Console → Realtime Database → Rules:

```json
{
  "rules": {
    ".read": true,
    ".write": true
  }
}
```

